        <briefdescription>
<para>accepts two <formula id="0">$ x$</formula>-monotone curves <computeroutput>xc1</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>xc2</computeroutput> and determines whether they can be merged to form a single <formula id="0">$ x$</formula>-monotone curve. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><computeroutput>xc1</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>xc2</computeroutput> are mergeable if their underlying curves are identical, they share a common endpoint, and they do not bend to form a non- <formula id="0">$ x$</formula>-monotone curve. <simplesect kind="pre"><para>The target point of <computeroutput>xc1</computeroutput> and the source point <computeroutput>xc2</computeroutput> coincide or the source point of <computeroutput>xc2</computeroutput> and the target point <computeroutput>xc2</computeroutput> coincide. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
